# Packaging Application into Standalone Executable

This plan outlines the steps to bundle the Flask web application and all its dependencies (HIS Client, binary templates, static assets) into a single Windows executable ([.exe](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/python_installer.exe)) for easy deployment.

## Proposed Changes

### [NEW] [resource_utils.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/resource_utils.py)
- Create a utility to resolve file paths correctly whether running from source or from a PyInstaller bundle (using `sys._MEIPASS`).

### [MODIFY] [his_client_final.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/his_client_final.py)
- Use `resource_path` from `resource_utils.py` for all [.bin](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/body_985.bin) template loads.

### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/app.py)
- Use `resource_path` for `templates` and `static` folder configuration.
- Add a mechanism to open the web browser automatically upon startup.

### [NEW] [build.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/build.py)
- A Python script to automate the `PyInstaller` command with all necessary flags:
    - `--onefile`: Bundle everything into one EXE.
    - `--add-data`: Include `templates`, `static`, and [.bin](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/body_985.bin) files.
    - `--name`: Internal tool name.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run the build script and verify the generated [.exe](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/python_installer.exe) exists in the `dist/` folder.
- Execute the [.exe](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/python_installer.exe) and confirm:
    1. The Flask server starts without errors.
    2. The browser opens to `http://localhost:5000`.
    3. Login and patient details work correctly (verifying [.bin](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/body_985.bin) files are loaded).

### Manual Verification
- Test the [.exe](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/python_installer.exe) on a computer without a Python environment installed.
